03/03/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The defence ministers of countries in Southeast Europe will meet in Zagreb on Friday (March 6th), media reported. 
The informal meeting will focus on challenges to regional security and new co-operation opportunities within the framework of the Adriatic Charter, an association created by Albania, Croatia and Macedonia in 2003. 
Last year, Montenegro and Bosnia and Herzegovina joined. 
Attending Friday's meeting will be the defence ministers of Croatia, Albania, Bulgaria, Greece, Hungary, Italy, Macedonia, Romania, Serbia, Slovenia and Turkey, as well as NATO representatives. 
(Javno, Focus - 03/03/09)
